night and the city is a 1950 film noir directed by jules dassin and starring richard widmark , gene tierney and googie withers . it is based on the novel of the same name by gerald &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; . shot on location in london and at shepperton studios , the plot revolves around an ambitious hustler whose plans keep going wrong . director dassin later confessed that he never read the novel the movie is based upon . in an interview appearing on the criterion collection dvd release , dassin recalls that the casting of tierney was in response to a request by darryl zanuck , who was concerned that personal problems had rendered the actress " suicidal , " and hoped that work would improve her state of mind . the film 's british version was five minutes longer , with a more upbeat ending and featuring a completely different film score . dassin endorsed the american version as closer to his vision . the film contains a very tough and prolonged fight scene between &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; , a celebrated professional wrestler in real life , and mike mazurki , who before becoming an actor was himself a professional wrestler , which leads to the death of &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; 's character .